00:23:38,278 --> 00:23:40,680
Hey there, I wanted to ask a question about the thing

477
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:42,622
about the giving credit back to the community

478
00:23:42,662 --> 00:23:43,542
as opposed to individuals.

479
00:23:43,703 --> 00:23:44,763
So you're the naming thing,

480
00:23:45,044 --> 00:23:46,485
and I've got a couple things like that in my game.

481
00:23:46,505 --> 00:23:49,547
So did you not mention the community members

482
00:23:49,607 --> 00:23:50,648
that came up with the names at all,

483
00:23:50,668 --> 00:23:53,430
and you just said this is a community-generated name?

484
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:55,171
Or how did that work more specifically?

485
00:23:55,499 --> 00:23:59,321
So in specifics to the example that I gave about the party name combinations,

486
00:24:00,282 --> 00:24:03,604
I did not give any credit specifically to any of the members who came up with them.

487
00:24:04,284 --> 00:24:08,867
What happened though is after we released them, I put a huge list of all the names that had made it in,

